The paper deals with the problem of lifelong learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a framework that involves deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from automatic machine learning (AutoML), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm also involves network compression, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on four different datasets, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
